[[ja:パピルス・カルルスベルグ1]] [[de:Papyrus Carlsberg 1]] [[sn:Papyrus Carlsberg 1]]

The '''Papyrus Carlsberg 1''' (also '''pCarlsberg 1, PC1''') contains texts concerning the {{ill|Book of Nut|de|Nutbuch|ja|ヌトの書|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, which date from the second century A.D. and originate from {{ill|Tebtynis|de|Tebtynis|ja|テブティニス|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. It is currently housed at the Egyptological Institute of the {{ill|University of Copenhagen|de|Universität Kopenhagen|ja|コペンハーゲン大学|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The content from PC1 was first published in 1940, with a further publication following in 1960.
It is a {{ill|Hieratic script|de|Hieratische Schrift|ja|ヒエラティック文字|lt=hieratic text|lt_de=hieratischen Text|lt_ja=ヒエラティックテキスト|qq=draft|qq=draft}} featuring a {{ill|Demotic language|de|Demotische Sprache|ja|デモティック言語|lt=demotic translation|lt_de=demotischer Übersetzung|lt_ja=デモティック翻訳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and accompanied by a demotic commentary. The {{ill|Papyrus|de|Papyrus|ja|パピルス|qq=draft|qq=draft}} consists of seven {{ill|column layout|de|Spaltensatz|ja|列組|lt=columns|lt_de=Kolumnen|lt_ja=列|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, four {{ill|recto|de|recto|ja|表|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and three {{ill|verso|de|verso|ja|裏|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, each containing 44 characters. PC1 is largely preserved apart from its beginning.
The papyrus measures 67.5&nbsp;cm in length, with a page height of about 30&nbsp;cm; the height of the writing mirror is 24.8&nbsp;cm. The column width varies between 14.3 and 17.2&nbsp;cm. The columns are arranged as follows: recto III corresponds to verso V, recto II corresponds to verso VI, and recto I corresponds to verso VII; recto IV stands alone and has no corresponding verso entry.
The text, written in demotic script, comprises the Nut depiction. The decan lists are missing. The papyrus ends abruptly after the first sentence of the lunar chapter.
== See also == * {{ill|Papyrus Carlsberg 1a|de|Papyrus Carlsberg 1a|ja|カルルスベルグパピルス1a|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
== Literature == * Hans-Otto Lange, {{ill|Otto Neugebauer|de|Otto Neugebauer|ja|オットー・ノイゲバウアー|qq=draft|qq=draft}}: ''Papyrus Carlsberg No. 1 Ein hieratisch-demotischer kosmologischer Text.'' Munksgaard, Copenhagen 1940. * {{ill|Otto Neugebauer|de|Otto Neugebauer|ja|オットー・ノイゲバウアー|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Richard-Anthony Parker|de|Richard-Anthony Parker|ja|リチャード＝アンソニー・パーカー|qq=draft|qq=draft}}: ''{{ill|Egyptian astronomical Texts|de|Egyptian astronomical Texts|ja|エジプト天文学テキスト|lt=Otto Neugebauer Bibliography|lt_de=Otto Neugebauer Bibliographie|lt_ja=オットー・ノイゲバウアーの書誌|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.'' (EAT), Volume 1: ''The early decans.'' Brown University Press, Rhode Island 1960, pp. 36–87.
